  "prompt": "What are the top rated Hollywood movies in 2017?",
  "response": "In 2017, several Hollywood movies received critical acclaim and high ratings. Here are some of the top-rated films from that year:\n\n1. **\"Get Out\"** \u2013 Directed by Jordan Peele, this horror-thriller was praised for its social commentary and suspenseful storytelling.\n\n2. **\"Lady Bird\"** \u2013 Directed by Greta Gerwig, this coming-of-age film received acclaim for its performances, particularly Saoirse Ronan\u2019s, and its heartfelt narrative.\n\n3. **\"Dunkirk\"** \u2013 Directed by Christopher Nolan, this World War II epic was celebrated for its immersive experience and technical achievement.\n\n4. **\"The Shape of Water\"** \u2013 Directed by Guillermo del Toro, this romantic fantasy received praise for its storytelling, performances, and visual style. It went on to win the Academy Award for Best Picture.\n\n5. **\"Call Me by Your Name\"** \u2013 Directed by Luca Guadagnino, this romantic drama was acclaimed for its performances, direction, and screenplay.\n\n6. **\"Coco\"** \u2013 Produced by Pixar, this animated film was noted for its stunning visuals, music, and emotional depth.\n\n7. **\"Blade Runner 2049\"** \u2013 Directed by Denis Villeneuve, this sequel to the 1982 classic was lauded for its visual effects, cinematography, and thoughtful storytelling.\n\n8. **\"The Florida Project\"** \u2013 Directed by Sean Baker, this drama was praised for its poignant storytelling and strong performances, particularly by Willem Dafoe.\n\nThese films were recognized at various award shows and by critics, solidifying their status as some of the best films of 2017.",
